definitions.definition: Any building or complex of buildings in which a legislature meets .
examples: The state capitol is located smack-dab in the middle of the state's capital .

definitions.definition: Any citadel or complex of buildings similar to the Roman Capitol , particularly Italian and Roman citadels including temples to Jupiter , Juno , and Minerva .
Alternative form of capitoul ( “ the former chief magistrates of Toulouse, France ” ) .

main_definition: ( US ) Any building or complex of buildings in which a legislature meets .
